HEADWORD: Periblast
<hw>Per"i*blast</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>periblasta`nein</grk> to grow around. See <er>Peri-</er>, and
<er>-blast</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>The protoplasmic matter
which surrounds the entoblast, or cell nucleus, and undergoes
segmentation.</def> -- <wordforms><wf>Per`i*blas"tic</wf>,
<pos>a.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

